vlanVoiceAgingTimeout.name: vlanVoiceAgingTimeout
vlanVoiceAgingTimeout.description: The vlanVoiceAgingTimeout indicates the time (in units of minutes) from when the last OUI MAC was ageout from the FDB the port will be removed from the Voice VLAN. The default value for vlanVoiceAgingTimeout object is 1440 minutes (24 hours). The value of this object must be restored from non-volatile storage after a re-initialization of the management system.

vlanVoiceTable.name: vlanVoiceTable
vlanVoiceTable.description: A table containing static configuration information for each voice VLAN configured into the device and dynamic port membership. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device is reset.

vlanVoiceEntry.description: Information for a voice VLAN configured into the device by management.

vlanVoiceOUIEntry.name: vlanVoiceOUIEntry
vlanVoiceOUIEntry.description: Information for a voice VLANs OUI MAC Prefixes configured into the device by management.

vlanVoiceOUIPrefix.name: vlanVoiceOUIPrefix
vlanVoiceOUIPrefix.description: The index value used to identify the OUI MAC Prefix component associated with this entry. The value of this object is used as an index to the vlanVoiceOUITable. Voice VLANs OUI Prefix is the first 3 most significant octets of the MAC address.

vlanVoiceOUIDescription.name: vlanVoiceOUIDescription

vlanVoicePortEntry.name: vlanVoicePortEntry
vlanVoicePortEntry.description: Static and dynamic per port information for a voice VLAN.

vlanVoicePortEnable.name: vlanVoicePortEnable
vlanVoicePortEnable.description: Enable this port to be a candidate to be added into the Voice VLAN.

vlanVoicePortVlanIndex.name: vlanVoicePortVlanIndex
vlanVoicePortVlanIndex.description: The Voice VLAN-ID the port is a candidate to be in.

vlanVoicePortSecure.name: vlanVoicePortSecure
vlanVoicePortSecure.description: Specify this port to be in Secure Mode when entering the Voice VLAN. In Secure mode only frames with MAC prefix matched to one of the OUI table prefixes are accepted, otherwise dropped.

vlanVoicePortCurrentMembership.name: vlanVoicePortCurrentMembership
vlanVoicePortCurrentMembership.description: Port's current status of membership in Voice VLAN. Port's possible values of membership in Voice VLAN: 'Active(1)' - Port is currently added to a Voice VLAN . 'NotActive(2)' - Specifies either that port is a candidate to be in Voice VLAN or disabled.

vlanVoiceOUISetToDefault.name: vlanVoiceOUISetToDefault
vlanVoiceOUISetToDefault.description: The vlanVoiceOUISetToDefault indicates that vlanVoiceOUITable should be set to it's default values if existed (OUI default prefixes). To do so the vlanVoiceOUITable should be previuosly deleted by usual entries destroying. This object behaviors as write-only than reading this object will always return 'false'.
